This paper deals with the automatic optimization of robotic behavior, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The optimization is based on the divergence of the optical flow field of a downward looking camera, which is a computer vision technique (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of neurocontrollers, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of abstraction on the input and output of the controller is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO and cs.CV, followed by cs.SY, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
